Content:
``save``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7661] To watch the progress when saving large files you can now pass the 
``--progress``
 flag to 
``save``
.

It gives information about the throughput and an interactive progress bar if available.
Progress for saving a file
íŸ@f5b3e9614b16df8d52310620ad56f0e5d6cb56fa336cd3e4d2efee24a26f063a⁄pTitle: title: Nushell 0.75
Path: Breaking changes
Content:
Unicode escapes in strings now use and extended format 
``\u{X...}``
, any scripts using the old syntax 
``\uXXXX``
 will have to be updated. See also 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7883] #7883
.
The 
``to url``
 command has been renamed and moved to 
``url build-query``
 as this better reflects is role as a nushell specific 
``url``
 command compared to a conversion. (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7702] #7702
)
``fetch``
 has been renamed to 
``http get``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7796] #7796
)
``post``
 has been renamed to 
``http post``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7796] #7796
)
Quotes are trimmed when escaping to 
``cmd.exe``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7740] #7740
)
``parse -r``
 now uses zero-indexed rows and uncapitalized columns (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7897] #7897
)
``last``
, 
``skip``
, 
``drop``
, 
``take until``
, 
``take while``
, 
``skip until``
, 
``skip while``
, 
``where``
, 
``reverse``
, 
``shuffle``
, 
``append``
, 
``prepend``
 and 
``sort-by``
 raise error when given non-lists (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7623] #7623
)
``to csv``
 and 
``to tsv``
 now throw error on unsupported inputs (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/7850] 7850
)
